text.tspan: Pneumococcal vaccine vs. diphtheria-tetanus-pertussis vaccine coverage, 2021
The percentage of one-year-olds who have received three doses of the combined diphtheria, tetanus toxoid and
pertussis (DTP3) vaccine against the percentage of one-year-olds who have received three doses of pneumococcal
conjugate vaccine (PCV3), in a given year.
Data source: WHO, Global Health Observatory
